@S. Pfeifer 
Hello, 6th period science!

You made some good observations and asked some great questions! Do you have any ideas where you might find answers to some of your questions? Are there any we can't know the answer to?

@Devyn D 

Interesting observation about the rise in the 1940s. Can you think of anything that happened that might be responsible for that? And then it fell a bit before rising again. Any thoughts about what could be causing it?

Also, that's a good observation about how much it fluctuates year to year.

@Sophie and Lainey 

Love hearing from my fellow Minnesotans!

Interesting observation about the spike around 1944. Great insight to think about what went on in the world to try to explain what you see in the graph!

@Team Mehh 
Good questions!  I also love your headline. 
It is amazing that Earth floats in space at just the right distance from the sun in order to be not too hot and not too cold. But an increase in temperature certainly would become dangerous at some point.

@Hannah & Logan 

Another contribution from my home state!

You pose some important questions. In what way do you think technology might influence temperatures? Do you think we could use technology to influence temperatures in the other direction?

@Mr. Kingsbury's class 
